fix(phase-T1): emergency roles backfill + auth/onboarding hardening

Four items from the T.1 review.

1) BLOCKER — migration 20260611_03 stamped every existing user with
   roles={buyer} while the SAME deploy added ROLE_REQUIRED gates on
   product-create / property-create, so real publishers were 403d in
   prod with no UI to recover from. Backfill migration applied via
   Management API:
   - users owning a shop with >=1 product -> +seller (4 users)
   - users owning >=1 property -> +agent (2 users)
   - bare shop owners with no products and no properties -> +seller
   Sanity: users_with_products == users_tagged_seller (4),
            users_with_properties == users_tagged_agent (2). Done.

2) silent-outage hardening: otp-verify and email-signin destructured
   away the user/row select error. A schema/transport hiccup
   masqueraded as AUTH_INVALID_CREDENTIALS or a 200 with a null user.
   Both fns now throw INTERNAL_ERROR 500 on real select errors ; legit
   misses (no such email) still flow through the constant-time bcrypt
   path. Both redeployed (otp-verify v22, email-signin v23).

3) profile-setup polish:
   (a) re-entrancy guard + Button loading/disabled while
       updateProfile.isPending,
   (b) step-0 gate uses !name.trim() (whitespace name now blocked
       before it can reach the server CHECK),
   (c) catch path actually saves display_name + city into the auth
       store, so the toast message is true. Copy now says
       "Profil sauvegardé sur cet appareil - verifie ta connexion."

4) setRoles() drift: also patches the auth.userJson MMKV snapshot and
   the in-memory user.roles so a boot reads matching roles from both
   slots ; server payloads still supersede on next sign-in.
